    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A doctrine deriving from a schism that occurred in Christian North Africa ca. 311 CE. The Donatists arose due to a disagreement over the election of Cæcilian as the Bishop of Carthage. The local bishops consecrated Donatus, a rival, for whom the sect is named. Occasionally persecuted, the sect survived until the Islamic conquest, during the 7th-8th centuries.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
